lenders.name: zak
lenders.loan_because:
I believe that the best way to make a difference in the developing world is through entrepreneurialism. In many developing countries women entrepreneurs are an untapped resource who hold amazing potential for their communities and countries. Through micro-finance they're given the financial support they need to turn their ideas and dreams into revenue (and job) producing entities. 

I believe that business education of these same people is also extremely important and extremely valuable. Unfortunately all that I can give at this time in my life is my money. I hope that in the future I'll be able to also give my time to help coach, mentor, and train willing entrepreneurs in the developing world to grow their businesses into successful ventures. Ventures that will help their countries to have more money, more education, and all the things that come along with this.
lenders.occupational_info: I own a chain of olive oil and balsamic vinegar tasting shops in the Northeast. I also am a partner of Crowdfund Capital Advisors (CCA), I co-authored the crowdfunding portions of the Jobs Act (which legalized equity and debt based crowdfunding), and co-authored Crowdfund Investing for Dummies.
